Column Comment.0: ANALYSIS IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a sample analysis. Various types ofanalysis may be conducted on a sample. Samples may be derived from lithologiccuttings, fluid collection etc.
Column Comment.1: ANALYSIS SOURCE: The source that the analysis came from, this could be a labtechnician, a lab, a company, a government agency, etc.
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currentlyeither active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: ANALYSIS DATE: Date the laboratory performed the gas analysis.
Column Comment.4: ANALYSIS PURPOSE: A narrative description of the purpose or objective of theanalysis.
Column Comment.5: ANALYSIS QUALITY: Describes standard quality indicators. For example poor, good,very good or excellent.
Column Comment.6: BASE DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the base of the analysis interval.
Column Comment.7: BASE DEPTH OUOM: Base measured depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.8: STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit thatwas studied in this analysis
Column Comment.9: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.10: END DATE: The date on which this analysis ended.
Column Comment.11: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.12: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.13: RECEIVED DATE: Date the sample was received by the laboratory for analysis.
Column Comment.14: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.15: REPORTED DATE: Date the sample analysis was reported by the laboratory.
Column Comment.16: REPORTED TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH: The reported depth of a well measuredvertically from the surface to the point of interest in the well bore. These reportedvalues may not represent the actual TVD as derivable from the directional survey andmay consequently be in error.
Column Comment.17: REPORTED TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE:
Column Comment.18: SAMPLE DATE: Date the sample was collected.
Column Comment.19: SAMPLE LOCATION: Describes the various locations that samples can be extractedfrom. For example in a well samples may be derived from the well head, shaker, mudpit, core or wellbore. Outside the well a sample may be taken from a road allowance,a waste pit, a water supply, etc.
Column Comment.20: START DATE: The date on which this analysis started.
Column Comment.21: STRATIGRAPHIC NAME SET NAME: a unique name of the set of stratigraphicnames to which the STRAT UNITS belong. A stratigraphic name set is a collection ofstratigraphic units, such as may be in use for a geographic area, a project, acompany etc.
Column Comment.22: STUDY TYPE: The type of study that is described, such as organic geochemistry,maceral analysis, paleontological analysis, benchmark environmental study, etc
Column Comment.23: TOP DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the top of the analysis interval.
Column Comment.24: TOP DEPTH OUOM: Top measured depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.25: STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit thatwas studied in this analysis
Column Comment.26: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.27: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.28: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.29: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.30: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.31: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.32: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
